  "aboutText": "Anthurium corrugatum is a compact, epiphytic Anthurium native to the humid wet tropical forests and cloud forests of Ecuador and northwestern South America. It forms a compact rosette from a basal crown and short stem, supported by a dense mass of roots. The leaves are spectacular and highly textured, being strongly corrugated and bullate with a thick, leathery feel. The leaf blades are elongated cordate with a narrow sinus, showing a striking quilted venation. Its growth is non-climbing and self-supporting.",
